[{"id":41811,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Since both the vectors are same, they will be parallel to each other. We know that vector&nbsp;product of two parallel vectors is zero.</p><p>Hence,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;is the correct answer.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41866,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4aa80495-9919-48d9-9174-2a199791e1de-image.png\" style=\"width: 279px; height: 150px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>180</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p>For small <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#8771;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41804,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Heat generated through resistance is given by,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>H</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>i</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi><mi>t</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, the percentage error in the calculation can be found by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><mi>H</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow><mi>i</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><mi>H</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><mi>H</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41862,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup><mi>&#160;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>%</mi><mtext>&#160;error&#160;in</mtext><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mi>%</mi></math><br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41760,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["0.1","0.8","0.7","0.6"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\text { Fractional error }=2 \\frac{\\Delta X}{X}+\\frac{3}{2} \\frac{\\Delta Y}{Y}+\\frac{2}{5} \\frac{\\Delta Z}{Z} \\\\ & =2(0.1)+\\frac{3}{2}(0.2)+\\frac{2}{5}(0.5) \\\\ & =0.2+0.3+0.2=0.7\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (8 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41867,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Error in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> can be calculated as<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.&nbsp;<br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Total time for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>oscillation is <math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>T</mi></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>= time for oscillation.<br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>&#160;t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>.&nbsp;<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;is</mo></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>90</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><math><mo>=</mo><mn>0.5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2.22</mn></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2.72</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8773;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41873,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$5,1,2$","$5,1,5$","$5,5,2$","$4,4,2$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2010","image":null},{"id":41863,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Percentage error in surface tension&nbsp;<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>D</mi></mrow><mi>D</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0.01</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.25</mo></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.01</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1.45</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>%</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.01</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1.25</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.01</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1.45</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1.489</mn><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>1.5</mn></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (02 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41872,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["increase by $0.2 \\%$","decrease by $0.2 \\%$","decrease by $0.05 \\%$","increases by $0.05 \\%$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{R} \\propto \\ell^2$ (for a given volume)\n$$\n\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{R}} \\%=\\frac{2 \\Delta \\ell}{\\ell} \\%\n$$\nThus when wire is stretched by $0.1 \\%$ resistance increases by $0.2 \\%$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2011","image":null},{"id":41774,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\pi}{4}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{6}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{2}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{3}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{P}}=\\cos (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\sin (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{j}} ;|\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{P}}|=1 \\\\ & \\because \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{P}}=\\mathrm{m} \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{v}} \\\\ & \\therefore \\hat{\\mathrm{P}}=\\hat{\\mathrm{v}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\hat{\\mathrm{v}}=\\cos (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\sin (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{j}} \\\\ & \\hat{\\mathrm{a}}=\\frac{-\\mathrm{k} \\sin (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\mathrm{k} \\cos (\\mathrm{kt}) \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}}{\\mathrm{k}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\hat{\\mathrm{a}}=-\\sin k t \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\cos \\mathrm{kt} \\hat{\\mathrm{j}} \\\\ & \\because \\hat{\\mathrm{F}}=\\hat{\\mathrm{a}}=-\\sin \\mathrm{kt} \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\cos \\mathrm{kt} \\hat{\\mathrm{j}} \\\\ & \\cos \\theta=\\frac{\\hat{\\mathrm{F}} \\cdot \\hat{\\mathrm{P}}}{|\\hat{\\mathrm{F}}||\\hat{\\mathrm{P}}|}=-\\frac{\\sin \\mathrm{kt} \\cos \\mathrm{t}+\\sin \\mathrm{kt} \\cos \\mathrm{t}}{1 \\times 1}=0 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\theta=\\frac{\\pi}{2}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41826,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Direction of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>|</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p>Direction of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>|</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>Angle between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#183;</mo><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><msub><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#177;</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (22 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41870,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$1 \\%$","$2 \\%$","$6 \\%$","$3 \\%$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given : $\\frac{\\Delta I}{I} \\times 100=2 \\%$;\n$\\frac{\\Delta R}{R} \\times 100=1 \\%$ and $\\frac{\\Delta t}{t} \\times 100=1 \\%$\nHeat produced, $H=I^2 R t$\nMaximum possible error in heat produced,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\frac{\\Delta H}{H} \\times 100 \\\\\n& =2\\left(\\frac{\\Delta I}{I} \\times 100\\right)+\\frac{\\Delta R}{R} \\times 100+\\frac{\\Delta t}{t} \\times 100 \\\\\n& =2 \\times 2 \\%+1 \\%+1 \\%=6 \\%\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":41789,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The given quantity is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><msqrt><mi>d</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p><p>The percentage error for a quantity can be given by the formula&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math>.</p><p>Relation of the relative errors will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow><mi>b</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Hence, the percentage error is calculated by substituting the values,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>%</mo></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41876,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$11 \\%$","$21 \\%$","$42 \\%$","$10 \\%$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{T}=2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{\\mathrm{l}}{\\mathrm{g}}} ; \\log \\mathrm{T}=\\log (2 \\pi)+\\frac{1}{2} \\log \\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{l}}{\\mathrm{g}}\\right) \\Rightarrow \\log \\mathrm{T}=\\log (2 \\pi)+\\frac{1}{2} \\log (1)-\\frac{1}{2} \\log (\\mathrm{g})$\nDifferentiating\n\n\n$\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{T}}{\\mathrm{T}}=0+\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{l}}{\\mathrm{l}}-0 \\Rightarrow \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{T}}{\\mathrm{T}} \\times 100=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{l}}{\\mathrm{l}} \\times 100$                           $=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 21=10.5 \\approx 10 \\%$\nNote: In this method, the $\\%$ error obtained is an approximate value on the higher side. Exact value is less than the obtained one.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":41848,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>v</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>v</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ufkuzwqpopglogewmlmccljrfcejmilearjzrjhbxinxshgvcl.png\" /> <br/><br/> <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><msup><mrow><mn>60</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41808,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Volume of the wire is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></math>.</p><p>Density of the wire is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#961;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Relative error in measurement of density</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>&#961;</mi></mrow><mi>&#961;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>006</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>005</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;Percentage error in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#961;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 1)","image":null}]